7 de enero de 2016

Goal and Description

The goal of this project was to allow users to determine which regions of Costa Rica are the most or least expensieve to live on. This was achieved by creating a map of the regions in which each region has a color. The hue/intensity of that color represents the median price by squater meter for that region.

## Conclusions

The most expensieve areas in Costa Rica are near the GAM, centered around Santa Ana. There are other expensieve areas near the coasts such as Jaco (Garabito) and Guanacaste (Hojancha, Carillo) which are regions with a lot of tourism.

Next steps

Next step would be to create a simple machine learning algorithm over this data. It would attempt to predict the overall price of a terrain.
